Install: sudo apt install ./eblink-debian-amd64.deb
Remove:  sudo dpkg  --remove eblink-debian-amd64


The installer will also add the udev rules for the stlink.

The following environment variables are set and are avaibale after linux restart:

    EB_DEFAULT_PROBE=stlink
    EB_DEFAULT_SCRIPT=auto

So you can from every terminal launch EBlink with just "eblink -G"  of flash file from any folder with "eblink -F file=test.elf" etc
IF you need a particular script file you can just overrule the environment by "eblink -Ssilabs-auto -G"

Target control:   "eblink -Tcortex-m,halt", "eblink -Tcortex-m,reset=2" or "eblink -Tcortex-m,resume"

The package remove will delete all the EBlink related stuff.
    
Have fun.
